dbStoredQuestions.questionText: Apply and extend previous understandings of addition and subtraction to add and subtract rational numbers; represent addition and subtraction on a horizontal or vertical number line diagram. (This standard encompasses performing operations with integers and representing numbers on a number line, including using inequalities.)

standards.subject: Mathematics

rigor.justification: The document's items predominantly require procedural application of integer arithmetic (adding, subtracting, multiplying, dividing), graphing integers on a number line and writing inequalities, prime factorization, and evaluating expressions using order of operations. These tasks assess application of learned algorithms and representations rather than simple recall or complex multi-step reasoning.
